, genderspezifische Fragen, die transkulturelle Relevanz dieses Lesestoffs sowie die Rolle im Prozeß einer Popularisierung der Aufklärung in Deutschland, Frankreich, der Schweiz und den USA. Der Band knüpft an zwei Forschungsprojekte der Stiftung Volkswagen und der DFG an, die der Herausgeber mit Hans-Jürgen Lüsebrink und Jean-Yves Mollier realisiert hat.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCalendarxHistoryy18th century. 0aCalendarxHistoryy19th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aBEE, GUIDO, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBRANDES, HELGA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBÖNING, HOLGER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGREILICH, SUSANNE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHAUKE, MARIE-KRISTIN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKAPRAUN, CAROLINA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLÜSEBRINK, HANS-JÜRGEN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMEISE, HELGA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMESSERLI, ALFRED, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMIX, YORK-GOTHART, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMix, York-Gothart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMix, York-Gothart, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aREICHARDT, ROLF, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVOGEL, CHRISTINE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part 